    "en": {
      "title": "Profits from petrol and super diesel",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "With the revision of fuel prices by the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation, profits from petrol and super diesel have become profitable and a liter of diesel and kerosene have further lost.",
        "Accordingly, a liter of 95 octane petrol costs the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation Rs. 68.61 per liter, 92 octane petrol at Rs. 15.57, from super diesel to Rs. 20.27 crore profit.",
        "However, a liter of auto diesel costs the CPC Rs. 8.52 and a liter of kerosene costs 334 rupees."
      ],
